main event: A thin-walled brass tube was reported to have dropped from the sky in Wadsworth, Ohio on August 8, 1958.
interesting points: The object appeared to be made of yellow brass and had been used for various purposes, such as a fishing pole handle or lamp fixture.
The aluminum cap on one end had been brazed on and had hand-scratched numbers on it.
The object was examined and determined to be a common item, likely not a UFO.
The case was reported to the Air Technical Intelligence Center (ATIC) at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base for further analysis.
The object was eventually deemed not to warrant further laboratory examination.
result: Identified as a common brass object, not a UFO
photographs: No, the report does not include any photographs
